Hi there

Thanks for your interest in this issue. Unfortunately Confluence 5.6.5 has reached its End of Life date and this plugin is no longer available. However, please note that in [Confluence Server and Data Center 7.3|https://confluence.atlassian.com/doc/confluence-7-3-release-notes-983794557.html], we released the ability when on a page for all users to see a simple list of all the people who:
*  are allowed to view the space, via space permissions, and
*  are not prevented from viewing the page by page restrictions.

Head to [Check who can view a page|https://confluence.atlassian.com/doc/check-who-can-view-a-page-992678937.html] to learn more, or check out our new [Permissions best practices guide|https://confluence.atlassian.com/doc/permissions-best-practices-992678945.html].

Thanks
 Makisa | Senior Product Manager, Confluence Server and Data Center
