When you create an export, do not make the default export options as select all  as well as having everything expanded. 

Having everything selected by default results in inadvertent exports that can run long, cause time-outs, and affect the production instance's performance (when doing large exports, the overall performance of the product for all users has come to a crawl at times). 

When you expand everything, it can take many, many minutes to render if your space contains hundreds of pages (e.g. a knowledgebase).  Have it work like a page tree allow you to expand and collapse as needed for the user to select.  When you expand, you can then call and get the children.  This improves both performance and usability (when you have hundreds of pages in a space, it becomes very challenging to locate the pages you want to include).  If you can collapse and then expand and select, it also makes it it easier to locate and select or review what you have selected.

